clinical_study.brief_title: Real-world Therapy of ALK-positive NSCLC in Sweden: the Sequencing of ALK Tyrosine Kinase Inhibitor Drugs and Their Therapeutic Outcomes Based on Data From National Registers.
clinical_study.official_title: Real-world Study of Non-small Cell Lung Cancer Treatment With ALK-tyrosine Kinase Inhibitors (ALK TKI) in Sweden: Drug Sequencing, Treatment Duration and Overall Survival - A Retrospective Study Using Swedish Register Data

brief_summary.textblock: This study aims to explore for the first time how the different ALK TKIs have been sequenced in real-world clinical practice and with which outcomes for Swedish lung cancer patients

primary_outcome.measure: Median survival using Kaplan-Meier estimates, and proportion of patients alive after 5 and 6 years

secondary_outcome.measure: Duration Of Treatment (days) for ALK-inhibitor users

study_pop.textblock: Adult patients treated with ALK TKIs in Sweden between 2012 and 2019, identified via the national prescription register.

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:
-Inclusion criteria for ALK-positive NSCLC patients will be based on prescription data i.e. defines eligible patients as adult patients with at least one filled prescription of ALK-inhibitors identified by the national prescription register. Only prescriptions filled at pharmacies can be captured in prescription registers, as they do not include data on hospital drugs. ALK-inhibitor treatments for patients with NSCLC are given primarily outside of the hospital setting minimizing the selection bias under the inclusion criteria.
Exclusion Criteria:
-not applicable
